<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="mild-adj">mild <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /maɪld/    美 /maɪld/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>温和的；温柔的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He has too mild a nature to get angry, even if he has good cause. 
他性情十分温和，即使有充分的理由，他也不会动怒。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(天气) 温暖的；暖和的</strong></h4>
<p>反 cold </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a mild winter
暖和的冬天</p></div>

<h4 id="3-slight">3.★ <strong>轻微的；不严重的 (slight)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>mild sunburn
轻微的晒伤　</p><footer> 人教⑤ – 5</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He looked at her in mild surprise. 
他略显吃惊地看着她。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He suffered from a mild heart attack. 
他患有轻度心脏病。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>味淡的；不浓的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 hot </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>mild cheese 
味道清淡的奶酪</p></div></div>